工作描述
Operations Manager – Private Label
Coupang is one of the largest and fastest growing e-commerce platforms on the planet. We are on a mission to revolutionize everyday lives for our customers, employees and partners. We solve problems no one has solved before to create a world where people ask, “How did we ever live without Coupang?” Coupang is a global company with offices in Beijing, Los Angeles, Seattle, Seoul, Shanghai, and Silicon Valley.

Job Overview:

As our Operations Manager for Private Label Sourcing Team, you will be responsible for oversee the consolidation and storage warehouse operated by Coupang’s freight forwarder, managing the relationship with the forwarder.  This isn’t a typical operations role as it includes a program management component to coordinate between suppliers, in-stock, AP, legal and logistic providers as it relates to the warehouse operations, so am open to a wider range of candidates with less operations experience. This person will also help with managing the operational performance of the vendors and help improve the efficiency of their supply chain. To succeed in this role, you must be a visionary leader, builder and operator.

 

Key Responsibilities:

Track shipments from supplier to FC
Obtain proper documentations from suppliers and share with the freight forwarders
Optimize delivery network globally through consolidation
Analyze volume to maximize utilization of cargo space
Analyze volume to choose most efficient and cost effective mode of transportation
Track quoted to actual rates for Freight Forwarder Scorecard
Track rates by lane for future negotiations
Negotiate with freight forwarders and secure contract
 

Qualifications:

2+ years of Operations Manager, Importing, Transportation or Supply Chain experience
Bachelor’s Degree is a must
Take on ownership and must have willingness to actively solve new and various issues
Can dive deep to problem solve and be creative in finding solutions
Analytical with excellent communication skills
Strong knowledge of manufacturing and production methods
Cross-functional team collaboration
Experience in retail, merchandising is a plus
Experience user of Excel – Strong understanding of vlookups, pivot tables, and sumifs
Fluent in English is a must
Fluent in Korean is a plus
 

Preferred:

4+ years of Operations Manager, Importing, Transportation or Supply Chain experience
Fluent in both English and Korean
MBA